	SPACE	4,10
**	$ITL - INPUT TEXT LINE.
*
*	$ITL INPUTS A LINE FROM THE TERMINAL.
*
*	CHARACTER ARE ACCEPTED FROM THE TERMINAL, RUBOUT AND BACKSPACE
*	CHARACTERS ARE PROCESSED. WHEN A CARRIAGE RETURN IS ENTERED, 
*	$ITL RETURNS.
*
*	ENTRY	NONE
*	EXIT	(HL) = #ITLA
*		(A) = TEXT LENGTH
*	USES	A,F,H,L

$ITL.	CALL	$ITL			; INPUT LINE IN UPPER CASE
	JMP	$MLU			; MAP LINE TO UPPER

$ITL	LXI	H,ITLA
	JMP	$RTL			; READ TEXT LINE
